results.title: Alex's Great State Race Buffalo Wild Wings Fundraiser-Resource Center for Persons with Disabilities
results.description:
Join us at Buffalo Wild Wings near campus on Wednesday, November 13th for food and fun benefiting Alex's Great State Race! A portion of all proceeds from 11am-2am will be donated to our cause. Follow this link for the flyer you'll need to bring: https://www.rcpd.msu.edu/node/959

About Alex's Great State Race:
On the eve of the rivalry football game, MSU and U-M Army ROTC cadets will run the game ball from East Lansing to Ann Arbor in memory of Alex Powell. The event will begin at Demonstration Hall at 3 am to send off the cadets and will end in Ann Arbor (specific location TBD) where we will honor Alex Powell and thank all those who have supported us. All proceeds from the race will benefit both the RCPD at MSU and the Services for Students with Disabilities (SSD) at U-M in support of accessible higher education for students with disabilities!

Check out our website to learn more about Alex's Great State Race or donate below.more information...

results.title: Jerry Rice: America's Game—The NFL at 100
results.description:
Jerry Rice, Retired NFL Wide Receiver; Co-Author, America’s Game: The NFL at 100; Twitter @JerryRiceIn Conversation with Raj Mathai, Anchor, NBC Bay Area; Twitter @rajmathai
Football legend Jerry Rice is regarded as one of the best wide receivers to ever play in the NFL. He is a three-time Super Bowl champion and a member of the Pro Football Hall of Fame and College Football Hall of Fame.
Rice celebrates some of the most memorable moments in NFL history and reflects on his own love of the game. He offers a comprehensive look at the players and coaches that helped define and transform football to the cultural phenomenon it is today.
Location: Villa Ragusa, 35 S. 2nd St., CampbellTime: 6:15 p.m. check-in, 7 p.m. program Notes: Rice photo by Daymion Mardel
All ticket sales are final and nonrefundable.

results.title: Team Trump 45 Mega FUNdraiser
results.description:
Team Trump is holding a Mega FUN-raiser to help the Republican Party of Seminole County win elections from the President all the way down ballot. Is there anything better than Trump & Football? Join us for the Auction-of-the-Year. Bring your wallet and be ready to bid on Paint the Trump artwork, sports memorabilia, trips, and much, much more.
Friendly Confines is offering special deals AND has developed POTUS Punch and MAGA Juice just for our event! How fun is that? The auction event is from 6pm to 9pm. It is sponsored by Jason Brodeur for Florida Senate. 
And we have a new addition!! A VIP event from 5-6pm will add to the fun. A limited number of signed copies of Judge Jeanine Pirro's latest book, 'Radicals, Resistance, and Revenge' will be available, courtesy of John Hamlin. VIP tickets will be sold at the door. We ask that you line up at 4pm in the mall hallway. Tickets for the VIP event will be $40 per person or three for $100.
Hosted by The Republican Party of Seminole County and co-hosted by the Republican National Hispanic Assembly of Seminole County. All contributions are not tax-deductible. This ad is paid for by the Republican Party of Seminole County. 
 
FAQs
 
How can I contact the organizer with any questions?
Contact Chairman Linda Trocine via email: ChairmanTrocine@gmail.com
 
Do I have to bring my printed ticket to the event?
Please sign up for FREE on Eventbrite and bring your ticket. Seating in the venue is not guaranteed.  VIP tickets are sold at the door.
